title: For Sale:  Western Derringer 22lr
postcontent:
I have for sale a derringer made in 1968. It was imported and sold through herter's when they were in business from the late 1800s  up till 1981 when they filed bankruptcy. This one is in 22lr caliber. Has steel hammer, trigger, pins, screws and barrel inset into the casting. Not thin liners like a lot of the new derringers have but actual steel barrels inset into barrel casting. 

Has the eagle over N proof marks for nitro proofed. For smokeless powder. Also has the ULM proof house mark which is the stag antler and date of 68 next to it. Meaning it was proofed in 1968 when it was made. 

For anyone not familiar with the ulm proof house they are the ones who HK exclussively goes through and walther uses them as well as far back as WWII. They are a quality proofhouse and proof quality firearms in return. 

Marked Western Derringer, Made in Germany. Not made by rohm either. It has the Kaschie factory stamp under the grip and Kaschie manufactured lighters from 1923 to early 60s. Look up their lighters on ebay. 100 plus for alot of them.  They made lots of metal goods for the german military during WWII. Just as their lighters are quality and collectible so are their derringers. 

This derringer has nice grips, black plastic checkered, nickel plated finish, nice steel barrels with shine and crisp rifling. Locks up tight, fires great. Has a safety as well. Basically a copy of the Old West Remington model 95 derringers in 41RF.


Can call or text me REDACTED anytime. Can meet within a decent distance.

title: For Sale:  GECO FLARE GUN PACKAGE
postcontent:
For sale is a Geco 26.5mm all steel flare pistol. The Geco is made in Germany and was imported into the US in fairly limited quantities in the early 2000's. Sportsman's Guide and several other retailers sold them inexpensively then. However today they are nearly impossible to find. In my opinion the Geco is the highest quality, strongest and most interesting of all of these type pistols brought to US during the last 20 years. Many feel that the HK is a better pistol however I've owned both and unlike the Geco - the only steel part on the HK is the barrel as the entire frame is plastic.

This Geco is in original UNFIRED condition. Also included in this package is:

26.5 mm to .410/.45 Long Colt adapter that allows 2.5" & 3" .410 shotgun ammo or .45LC ammo to be safely fired.

26.5mm to 12 gauge adapter that allows the less expensive 12 gauge flares to be fired. This adapter cannot be used with regular 12 gauge shotgun shells and must never be attempted as the results would be catastrophic.

Original German flap holster that is weather resistant and has room to store the pistol, cleaning brush, 26.5mm ammo, .410 or.45 ammo & one or both adapters. Holster also has a shoulder carry strap attached.

26.5mm cleaning brush and nylon lanyard strap for pistol

(3) 5 round boxes 2.5" .410 rifled slug ammo. (1) 25 round box of 3" - 00 buck with 5 pellets per shell, & (1) 25 round box 3" #7.5 shot (devastating close range defense load).

(2) 26.5mm white parachute illumination shells, (2) 26.5 mm Red Rain shells & (2) 26.5mm orange smoke shells.

(1) sealed 4 round package of Orion 12 gauge super red flares - expire July 2016

The last Geco I saw on Gunbroker was before Christmas and it sold for over $200 without accessories similar to what the HK's do when they come up for sale. So if you investigate and price everything included in this set - you'll see that my asking price is a bargain.

Price: $350 obo. This is a pickup item as shipping live flare shells is a hassle and it's costly. Also because this flare pistol becomes a real firearm when the .410 adapter is inserted you must be at least 21 to purchase.

FYI, that is duct tape on the bottom of the mags. the steel is a nice, but slightly slippery finish, so I added some grip! 

Also thrown in is a Sniper Central Log book, a pair of good Simmons binoculars, and a kit with rags, tools, oils, the original trigger guard/magazine, and the drag bag. 

This is a complete kit with everything you need to maintain and store the rifle, as well as hit targets reliably out to....well, I've only shot it to 550 yards, and made cold bore hits every time on a 6x6" plate. This rifle is an excellent sub MOA rifle, and many builders seem to think remington has something going for them with these heavy barrels they manufacture. I've shot .5" groups at 100 yards with every well made factory ammo, FGMM, Hornady TAP, Black Hills Match etc.. The rifle likes it all, and I'm sure it will respond better to reloads.

I don't need to sell this rifle. I WANT to sell it, to help fund a 69 Camaro restoration. I will be glad to keep it rather than lose too much money selling it.

title: For Trade:  Beretta M9 with threaded barrel, 4 Hi-cap clips, low round count
postcontent:
The Beretta Model 9 is a semi-automatic pistol chambered in 9mm.

The M9 is the civilian version of the US military issued pistol. It is almost exactly the same as the M92 except it has distinctive military markings on the slide. Otherwise, it has an open slide design, so the barrel shows through. It has an external hammer that when cocked back changes the trigger pull from a double-action (long pull) to a single-action (short pull). An ambidextrous safety positioned also acts as a de-cocking lever and when pushed down it rotates the firing pin out of alignment. A second safety feature is its visible automatic firing pin block, which prevents the pistol from discharging if accidentally dropped.

The updated model, M9A1, has interchangeable back straps, so the grip can change for comfort or ease-of-use.  

I have the original box, paperwork and all the goodies.

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec KSG *very rare coyote tan finish*
postcontent:
I have for sale my uber rare LNIB Coyote Tan Kel-Tec KSG. The KSG alone is hard to find as is, but the coyote tan variant is nearly impossible. I’ve only shot a couple dozen rounds through it. I wouldn’t even consider that “broken in” yet. I’ve sighted-in the sights with slugs @ 50yds. It’s dead on every time (rounds touching bullseye), as long as you do your part. And I’ve shot some birdshots through it both slow and rapid fire to test its’ abilities using cheap birdshots. They all cycled flawlessly. Great compact shotgun for home defense/personal protection or just to add to your collection due to its’ rarity. 

The firepower you get from this very compact shotgun is very impressive. 14+1 rounds of regular 12ga shells, or 24+1 rounds of Aguila mini-shells. That’s comparable to a full mag of an AR! On a shotgun nonetheless. While testing it, I also got a good look at how well made the KSG is. Very well built and durable. Looks like it can withstand some major abuse. Here’s a couple of good videos showing how durable these KSG’s are: 

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QAcYErAoVP0

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a-cUJ-w-yjo

Another thing I love about the KSG is the trigger. If you’ve ever shot a bullpup before, you’ll know 1st hand how horrendous and heavy the trigger is. The KSG is by far the best bullpup trigger I’ve shot. Very crisp and light trigger. Enables the shooter to shoot faster and more accurately.

The reason I’m selling my KSG is because I recently found out that I cannot use this gun for the purpose I bought it for. This has nothing to do with the gun, but the agency I’m with. So sadly, I have no use for this gun. If I was a collector, I’d keep it just because of its’ rarity. But I’m more of a shooter and tend to get rid of guns that I don’t/won’t use.

Here’s what you get with this sale:
Kel-Tec KSG (factory coyote tan)
Magpul (MBUS) Rear sights (tan)
Magpul (MBUS) Front sights (tan)
Magpul RVG (vertical grip) (tan)
Kel-Tec KSG Kydex cheek rest
Kel-Tec KSG Handstop (tan)
Condor 28” compact tactical gun case (tan)-(perfect fit for KSG)
All original box, manuals, accessories, etc that came with the KSG from the factory

My asking price is $2500 FIRM for everything listed above. Serious inquiries only please. Not interested in any trades. Must meet face to face in Sugar Land area. CHL holder preferred, but not required. 

The reason why I posted my ad here 1st is because I’d rather sell locally, but will put it up on gunbroker if nobody’s interested locally.

If interested, text/call 832-451-4139 or email azn281tx@aol.com
